{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Gdxbffdv2YNEZKPBsVbDsD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the flow:\n\n1. Frontend `openDrawer()` fetches `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n2. Backend `handleAPIStepContent()` finds the workflow, gets the step, then tries to resolve file references\n\nLooking at the backend handler (line 1134-1196), it:\n1. Parses the workflow file\n2. Gets the step config\n3. Tries to resolve `file()` references via `resolveFileRef()`\n\nThe `resolveFileRef` function (line 1203-1213) looks correct - it checks for `file(\"...\")` syntax and reads the file.\n\n\nBut I'm seeing the issue now - when the handler tries to resolve the prompt file reference, if that fails silently, it just falls through without returning any content or error to the frontend.\n\nThen for command and script fields, it's calling `resolveFileRef` but ignoring errors and writing whatever comes back, which would be an empty string if the file doesn't exist. The real problem is in how `resolveFileRef` parses the `file()` syntax...\n\nParsing file references... So the file path resolution should work correctly — `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` would resolve to the full path on the host machine. The test at line 799 is passing, which is a good sign. Let me check the git diff to see what's actually changed in both the test and handler files.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5370,"cache_read_input_tokens":45968,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5370},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21e50bb8-a4d3-4e92-bbe7-da11fcd0636e","uuid":"1ec60961-0240-4c91-b3e4-4210ea997762"}
