{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014q1UyHNGstVD2NmF1JVtxn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is already implemented in the working tree. The changes look correct:\n\n1. **`handleAPIStepContent`** - Previously, for `prompt` configs with `file()` references, it was trying to read the raw value (e.g., `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`) as a file path directly via `os.ReadFile`, which would fail. Now it properly calls `resolveFileRef()` which parses the `file(\"...\")` DSL syntax and reads the actual file contents.\n\n2. **`resolveFileRef` helper** - New function that detects `file(\"path\")` syntax, extracts the path, reads the file, and returns contents. Plain strings are returned as-is.\n\n3. **Tests added** - `TestResolveFileRef` and `TestAPIStepContent_FileRef` verify the fix.\n\nLet me run the tests to confirm everything passes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2938,"cache_read_input_tokens":51338,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2938},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21e50bb8-a4d3-4e92-bbe7-da11fcd0636e","uuid":"b22af8a8-fad4-4ac2-88ea-5891f5f9621d"}
